The import statements importing library functions:
tkinter
sqlite3
OOP concept

1) Problem Statements:

Traditional quiz systems (paper-based or simple tools) are:
Time-consuming to manage
Difficult to evaluate instantly
Not interactive for users
There is a need for an automated, user-friendly quiz system with instant results.

2) Objectives:

To develop an interactive quiz system using Python
To implement a Graphical User Interface (GUI) using Tkinter
To store and manage quiz data using SQLite database
To apply Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) concepts like:
Classes
Inheritance
Methods
To provide:
Real-time quiz interaction
Timer-based quiz
Score tracking and history
To create an admin panel for adding questions dynamically

3) Features:

i) User Features:
Enter username before starting quiz
Attempt randomized quiz questions
Multiple question types:
Multiple Choice Questions (MCQ)
True/False
Timer-based quiz (60 seconds) 
Instant score calculation
Automatic result display

ii) Admin Features:
Add new questions through GUI
Supports:
MCQ (with 4 options)
True/False questions
Input validation and error handling

iii) Database Features (SQLite):
Stores:
Questions
User scores
Automatically initializes database
Saves quiz history with:
Username
Score
Total marks
Date & time

iv) History Tracking:
View past quiz attempts
Displays data in a table format
Sorted by latest attempts

v) Technical Features:
Built using Tkinter (GUI Framework)
Uses SQLite3 (Database)
Implements:
Exception Handling
Randomization of questions
Timer using after() method
Clean and modular code structure
